A .NET Temporal workflow uses `Workflow.CurrentDetails` to continuously update a rich Markdown status string as it progresses through dozens of long-running activity steps. A senior engineer reviewing the code raises a concern about replay safety. Which of the following best describes the actual risk and why it exists at the intersection of workflow determinism and UI metadata?

```csharp
[Workflow]
public class OrderWorkflow
{
    [WorkflowRun]
    public async Task RunAsync(string orderId)
    {
        Workflow.CurrentDetails = $"Starting order {orderId} at {DateTime.UtcNow}";
        await Workflow.ExecuteActivityAsync(
            (OrderActivities a) => a.ValidateAsync(orderId),
            new ActivityOptions { StartToCloseTimeout = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5) });
        Workflow.CurrentDetails = $"Validated at {DateTime.UtcNow}";
        await Workflow.ExecuteActivityAsync(
            (OrderActivities a) => a.FulfillAsync(orderId),
            new ActivityOptions { StartToCloseTimeout = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10) });
        Workflow.CurrentDetails = "Complete";
    }
}
```

An engineering team is building a .NET order-processing workflow that uses `StaticSummary` and `StaticDetails` on `WorkflowOptions` to populate the Temporal Web UI. They also attach a per-activity `Summary` to each `ActivityOptions` call. During a production incident, an operator tries to search the visibility store for workflows by filtering on their summary text (e.g., `StaticSummary = 'Order processing for customer #12345'`). The search returns no results. Which of the following correctly explains why, and what the interaction is between UI enrichment metadata and the visibility store's search attribute system?

```csharp
var handle = await client.StartWorkflowAsync(
    (OrderWorkflow wf) => wf.RunAsync(order),
    new WorkflowOptions
    {
        Id = $"order-{order.Id}",
        TaskQueue = "orders",
        StaticSummary = $"Order processing for customer #{order.CustomerId}",
        StaticDetails = $"Region: {order.Region}, Tier: {order.Tier}"
    });
```
